articles.author: Suban Abdulla, David Milliken
articles.title: UK exits recession with fastest growth in nearly three years - Reuters UK
articles.description: Britain's economy grew by the most in nearly three years in the first quarter of 2024, ending the shallow recession it entered in the second half of last year and delivering a boost to Prime Minister Rishi Sunak ahead of an election.

articles.title: Pasco: Rat remains found in Japanese bread triggers recall and refunds - BBC.com
articles.description: Pasco has recalled 104,000 packs of sliced bread after rat remains were found in its products.

articles.title: Bank of England 'optimistic' as it edges closer to summer rate cut - BBC.com
articles.description: Its comments came as UK interest rates were left unchanged at a 16-year high of 5.25%.
